The `sorry` occurs when trying to prove that `∫ ω, ∏ k, inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω) ∂μ = ∫ ω, ∏ k, inner ℝ (Y (I k).1 ω) (Y (I k).2 ω) ∂μ`. The `refine IdentDistrib.integral_eq ?_` tactic creates a goal for the `IdentDistrib` instance. The `sorry` is in the placeholder for this instance.

We need to provide the `IdentDistrib` instance for the product of terms. The terms `∏ k, inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω)` and `∏ k, inner ℝ (Y (I k).1 ω) (Y (I k).2 ω)` are products of terms that are identically distributed.

For each `k`, `inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω)` is identically distributed to `inner ℝ (Y (I k).1 ω) (Y (I k).2 ω)`. This is because `X j` is identically distributed to `Y j` for each `j`.

The product of identically distributed terms is also identically distributed. So we need to show that `fun ω ↦ ∏ k, inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω)` is identically distributed to `fun ω ↦ ∏ k, inner ℝ (Y (I k).1 ω) (Y (I k).2 ω)`.

