The final result is $\mathbb{E}\left[\left\| \sum_{i \in A} X_i \right\|^{2m}\right] \leq \text{marcinkiewiczZygmundSymmConst}(2m) \cdot \mathbb{E}\left[\left( \sum_{i \in A} \|X_i\|^2 \right)^m\right]$, which is the desired Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund inequality for symmetric random variables.
</think>
